.Dd October 17, 1997
.Dt MAKEWHATIS 8
.Sh NAME
.Nm makewhatis
.Nd create a whatis.db database
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm /usr/libexec/makewhatis
.Op Ar manpath
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
strips the NAME lines from compiled or raw
.Xr man 1
pages and creates
a whatis.db database
for use in
.Xr apropos 1
or with
.Xr man 1 's
.Fl k
option.
If
.Ar manpath
is unspecified,
.Nm
by default creates a database for /usr/share/man.
Man pages compressed with
.Xr compress 1
and
.Xr gzip 1
are uncompressed before processing, unformatted man pages
will be processed by
.Xr getNAME 8 .
.Sh BUGS
.Nm
should find its search paths using /etc/man.conf
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr man 1 ,
.Xr man.conf 5 ,
.Xr getNAME 8
.Sh AUTHOR
J.T. Conklin (jtc@netbsd.org)
